<br>
There is always those in EVERY class that say this. It's just the simple fact of life. If that is how you feel Grimstaff, then there is nothing really to argue about. It's your personal opinion, and I can respect that.<br>
<br>
I have stated they could make changes to wizards. It always bugs me to hear of changes for the better for many other classes but hardly any for wizards. The last spell change we got was to Okiels levity (a spell which made several other spells usless, give with one hand, take with another) to make it stackable.<br>
<br>
Necros and mages just got AA planar pet made better. Many classes got spell graphic changes, and our ice rain spells still look like fire. <br>
<br>
But I don't think wizards were built wrong, they just get ignored these days. Everyone always says that for the longest time, wizards were the top, but with all the changes in the last year, and expansions, things have changed. Possibly that is because not enough wizard players are giving feedback? I know I do. Many many mage players kept complaining till they finally did something. I suggest that every wizard player start sending in feedback to Sony.<br>
<br>
If you've been having these feelings for 4 years, Grimstaff, um this isn't some slam or put down, but ask yourself why you've stuck to playing a class that you've thought was never made right for 4 years? I mean, there has to be something about being a wizard you like? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 7910<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 11:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There is always one...</span><hr size=1> Never said I didn't LIKE the class.  Never said nor implied I hate it.  That's your addition to my statements, without basis or logic.  I mean seriously guys, if I point out problems with a car I like does that mean I despise the car?  Or that I'm frustrated and voice my frustration when it comes up?  Myztic either has an astonishingly selective memory or is deliberately ignoring the many things I've said about Wizards that are positive and constructive, but that's his perogative I guess.<br>
<br>
Here's what I mean about improperly designed class from the beginning: This game is built around the idea of opponents significantly tougher than the PCs, and the concept of experience gained only through very difficult encounters.  Further, the combat engine does not reflect fighting poorly when you are injured (for most monsters, its rather the opposite).  Thus, a class built around AE attacks and blasts without much defense and very low hit points and AC is going to have problems by design.  The game doesn't really support a high offense/low defense character very well, and that's a basic flaw with Mage and Wizard design.<br>
<br>
Further, the class was originally built around being the biggest boomer, and then was heavily cut back from their first design.  Two problems resulted from this: <br>
<br>
First, they put Direct Damage on too many other classes, which watered down the Wizard's design specialty significantly.<br>
<br>
Second, these cutbacks were not done with proper context of other classes.  Clerics, Druids, and Magicians all get more damaging blasts at odd points through the levels, pointing to an inconsistent and improperly examined design for Wizards and other classes.  These things were never addressed, and every attempt to get them addressed has been ignored or contemptuously dismissed (well, Absor pretty much did everything contemptuously).<br>
<br>
Further, as time went on, new spells added were FURTHER not done in proper context of all the classes.  Rangers, Druids, Shadow Knights and other classes all have gotten tremendously fast, good blasts that are far faster for the damage than anything Wizards have at that level.  Proper context would ensure Wizards would have at least something similar or perhaps just not giving these spells to the classes that they were granted to.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is that the class works, more or less, and you can enjoy yourself in any class in the game.  Its more about your friends and what you do than the class you play, EQ is like 90% socialization and 10% game.  Wizards are, as I stated earlier for those unable to read positive things I say, the most powerful DD class in the game almost every level.  By the end game, the edge has gotten very significant.  It's just too bad that edge is so blurred or ill-defined for so many other levels, and if it were me in charge of design, my pride at the job would prevent me from letting that happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silverbladetheenchanter>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1016<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/03 12:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is wizard the master of direct damage now?</span><hr size=1> As a mage, in a group I use my mana to:<br>
