<br>
Yes, at some levels mages have better vendor DD spells than wizards do.  I had the same problem when I was fighting seafuries at level 44 and my mage friend was outdamaging me.  But you grow out of it.  Personally, I'd much rather peak at the high end than at a mid-level where no one stays for long.<br>
<br>
A level 60 wizard easily outnukes a level 60 mage.  And a level 65 wizard easily outnukes a level 65 mage.  It's not even close.  Add in pet damage and yes, a mage can contribute more overall damage in a lot of xp groups, but that's fine with me.  There's not a mage in my guild who can come close to my damage output on big raid mobs.  And with the absurdly hard hitting PoP mobs, I can outsolo mages now too (which used to be their strength).<br>
<br>
